{"title":"Search and replace matches in the text","description":"This program allows you to find and replace sections of text, including using regular expressions and its flags such as ignoring case.","content":"## Search for matches and their replacement\r\nThis program allows you to find and replace sections of text. \r\nTo use regular expressions, enable the corresponding function in the settings. Now you will be able to make a replacement according to the regular expression template. In this program, there is no need to install boundary slashes in the template.\r\nIt is also possible to make a replacement both on a one-time basis and for each match separately.\r\nThe program provides the possibility of ignoring the case when searching for matches in a string.\n\n You can also familiarize yourself with other functionality of this online [text editor](/en/editor)."}